"""
        Test that a TypeError is raised when an invalid value is used to set
        the unique identifier of a MACSignatureKeyInformation struct.
        """
kwargs = {'unique_identifier': 0}
self.assertRaisesRegex(TypeError, 'Unique identifier must be a string.',
    objects.MACSignatureKeyInformation, **kwargs)
args = objects.MACSignatureKeyInformation(), 'unique_identifier', 0
self.assertRaisesRegex(TypeError, 'Unique identifier must be a string.',
    setattr, *args)
